From: AgentOS Runtime <runtime@agentos.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH] brush-core: spawn background jobs as real children

WASI cannot make progress on a background Tokio task while the foreground
shell is blocked in a managed child wait. More importantly, an internal task
has no process ID: `$!` is empty, an external `kill` cannot signal it, and
`wait` can hang forever after a script tries to terminate the job.

Spawn pipelines whose commands are proven external through the existing
process path. Run functions, builtins, aliases, dynamically expanded commands,
and compound lists in a new Brush child with the visible shell state restored.
Every background job consequently has a real guest PID and participates in
normal signal and wait semantics.

